    Allow JMods in project browser's external libraries list (#3629)

    Fixed mod element conversion method calling itself (#3481)
    
    * Fixed mod element conversion method calling itself
    
    * GE is null, so we handle it as such (original GE files will not belong to any ME so in workspace code regeneration, they will be removed anyways) + more verbose logging when converting
    
    * Revert previous fix, not the right approach
    
    * The most important part
    
    * Also quite important
    
    * Fixes to fix circular reference issues:
    
    - merged ME reinit and setworkspace, reinit only loads mcitems if ME type is known
    - when reloading MEs in workspace, a copy of ME list is made as ME list may change during this operation
    - when converting uknown GE type, original definition file is removed before deserializing JSON
    - procedure loading makes sure workspace reference is present
    
    Also did some other smaller cleanups and made some error prints more verbose while looking for the solution to the original bug.
    
    * Improve logs
    
    * Fix bug found by Goldorion

    * Improved circular reference prevention system

Date:   Wed Jul 20 13:28:37 2022 -0400

    Fix for the MacOS Image Maker tool dialog freeze. (#2996)
    
    * Fix for the Mac-OS "Create Texture From Scratch" blank window freeze.
    
    The freeze was caused by hiding the "block texture selection" panel before making the "New Image" sub-panel visible.
    
    This change does change behavior slightly. The selection window will now remain open underneath the "New Image" modal until you press cancel or create.
    
    * Adjusted the process(mouseEvent) method of several problematic tools.
    The dialogs are now made visible when the event dispatcher queue is ready via invokeLater().
    
    This fixes a MacOS crash caused by using the Colorize, Desaturate, HSVNoise, Resize Layer, and Resize Canvas tools.

commit 4cd517a33da0b2a4f1327279bcd24cc891c54be0
Author: Kaleb Luedtke <trenlymc@gmail.com>
Date:   Sun Dec 19 04:01:26 2021 -0600

    Use DisplayVersion key for NSI Script (#2152)
    
    * Use DisplayVersion key for NSI Script
    
    The `Version` key for uninstallers isn't as widely applicable as `DisplayVersion` is. By using `DisplayVersion` instead of `Version` it will allow for easier integration with other programs, package managers, and user scripts.
    
    * Fix accidental newline

1	1	platform/windows/installer/install.nsi

    * Removed try catch as discussed
    
    * Changed translation strings
    
    * [IMPORTANT] Bypassing existing APIs (BlocklyLoader system) and directly loading JSON for triggers
    
    * Added similar error set result block produces to cancel block too
    
    * Improved cancelable/has result display a bit
    
    Co-authored-by: KlemenDEV <klemen.pylo@gmail.com>
